1
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,567
<i>If you want to see Jessica,
come here now.</i>

2
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,200
<i> No, Dad! Don't listen to her!</i>

3
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,533
<i> Please, let Jessica go.</i>

4
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,467
<i>Didn't you say
that I'm just a burden to you?</i>

5
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,067
<i>You're only mine. Do you get it?</i>

6
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,400
<i> I still love you.</i>

7
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:52,233
<i>You really are an
ungrateful kid!</i>

8
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:55,100
<i>You don't want me and your dad
to get back together?</i>

9
00:00:55,233 --> 00:00:56,467
<i> Are you okay?</i>

10
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,367
<i> I can't keep a secret.</i>

11
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:00,500
<i> What secret, Mom?</i>

12
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:02,500
<i>Is this about
Coleen's father again?</i>

13
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,600
<i>You don't care about him, right?</i>

14
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:06,300
<i> So, just leave us be!</i>

15
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:08,567
<i> You're so rude!</i>

16
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:10,200
<i> Go ahead! Here!</i>

17
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,733
<i> Kill each other!</i>

18
00:01:11,867 --> 00:01:13,400
<i> I understand you</i>

19
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:15,833
<i>because you know how it feels
to have a father,</i>

20
00:01:15,967 --> 00:01:17,800
<i>and you got hurt because of him.</i>

21
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:18,867
<i> You love him so much.</i>

22
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,000
<i> Aren't you a daddy's girl?</i>

23
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:24,000
<i> He left us, Jeff.</i>

24
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:26,500
<i> It hurts to lose a father.</i>

25
00:01:28,567 --> 00:01:29,667
<i>Where do you think you're going?</i>

26
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,667
<i>Are you running away
from me again?</i>

27
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,267
<i> Jessica!</i>

28
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:40,600
Please eat for now.

29
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:44,267
Dear, I'm sorry. I really can't.

30
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,967
I'm worried about your sister.

31
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:49,233
Dad, I understand.

32
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:53,033
I'm also worried for Jessica.

33
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:56,700
But I trust that she can escape
her mom.

34
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,500
How?

35
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:03,500
I'm sure Miss Hazel isn't
going to stay up all night.

36
00:02:03,633 --> 00:02:06,000
Jessica is going to escape.

37
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:08,200
What if she tied Jessica?

38
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:09,700
Dear, please.

39
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:12,167
Book me a ride, and help me
get out of here.

40
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:12,900
Please.

41
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:13,967
Dad, don't.

42
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,167
Don't do that, Dad.

43
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,800
If you go to Miss Hazel,

44
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:20,367
she'll take you away
from me again.

45
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,233
We'll get separated again.

46
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:27,433
Here you go.

47
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:30,867
Here's Ma'am Felma's
special custard cake.

48
00:02:32,767 --> 00:02:34,500
Why did you bring
that out, Didang?

49
00:02:36,367 --> 00:02:37,500
Where's Mom?

50
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:42,700
Dear, I'm sorry,
but I have to do this.

51
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:45,567
Your sister's life
depends on this.

52
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:48,100
- Dad.
- Coleen, let's go.

53
00:02:48,267 --> 00:02:50,667
We need to go back to...

54
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,467
Dear, why are you crying?

55
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,233
Dad wants to go to Miss Hazel.

56
00:02:57,367 --> 00:02:59,433
Felma, I need to save Jessica.

57
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:01,133
You can't do that.

58
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:03,100
You might get caught.

59
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,933
Our children are outside.

60
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,400
Our children?

61
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:14,533
I'll look for them.

62
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:16,133
Where are you going?

63
00:03:16,267 --> 00:03:18,433
I'll look for Mom and Coleen.

64
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:20,533
I'll find out
what they're keeping from us.

65
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,467
No, have some desserts first.

66
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,400
Andrea, sorry.

67
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:28,133
It was an accident.

68
00:03:28,267 --> 00:03:29,733
Didang, you did it on purpose.

69
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:33,400
Wait.

70
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,700
Why would I do it on purpose?

71
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:36,800
You did it on purpose

72
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,667
because you're in cahoots
with Coleen and Mother!

73
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,433
Andrea, that's enough.

74
00:03:40,567 --> 00:03:42,233
Just change your clothes.

75
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:45,600
And can you please
pick up Tetay?

76
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:47,267
Bring her to your room.

77
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,300
And I'll also grab
some cleaning stuff.

78
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:50,600
- That's sticky.
- Come on, Didang!

79
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:51,367
I'm sorry.

80
00:03:58,133 --> 00:03:59,200
What's that?

81
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:01,633
What are you doing?

82
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:02,900
What are you trying to say?

83
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:04,667
- What's that?
- You're so slow.

84
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,333
I want to be alone with Daisy.

85
00:04:06,467 --> 00:04:07,833
So I want you to leave.

86
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,033
So, you want some
alone time with Daisy,

87
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:12,867
that's why you want me
to bring Tetay to my room

88
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,167
and stay there.

89
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,300
Why didn't you just say it?

90
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:17,833
Annoying!

91
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:19,000
She's so slow.

92
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:23,333
Where are we going?

93
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:24,500
Come on.

94
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,500
You want to get away
from Hazel, right?

95
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:34,800
Why would you willingly
go back to her?

96
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,800
She has Jessica.

97
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:38,433
There must be another way.

98
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,200
Something that has
a fighting chance.

99
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:42,700
Not the kind where you just
give up without a fight.

100
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:46,267
Do you want to suffer again
because of your wife?

101
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,467
Felma, what are my chances?

102
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,433
Look at my situation.

103
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:52,400
This is the only way I know
to save my daughter.

104
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:55,500
Do you want us to report
her to the police?

105
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:56,867
Will you help me?

106
00:04:58,167 --> 00:05:01,033
There's no way I can
leave you like that.

107
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,200
I don't want to get involved
in your problems anymore,

108
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:08,567
but I'll admit,
I'm worried about Jessica.

109
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,333
And besides, I want you both
to get out of here already.

110
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:13,300
You might get caught by...

111
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:15,467
by my kids.

112
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,100
There was already
a commotion here earlier.

113
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:22,733
Andrea already knows that Coleen
and me are keeping a secret.

114
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,767
Wait. I'll call someone I know.

115
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,233
Come in.

116
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,367
Maybe you haven't eaten yet.

117
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,200
Have something first.

118
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,267
No, it's okay. I'm still full.

119
00:05:43,167 --> 00:05:46,933
Classmate, I thought
you no longer needed my service.

120
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:48,767
I lost her.

121
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,100
What?

122
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:51,600
A kid managed to get away
from you?

123
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,533
Don't get mad.

124
00:05:58,667 --> 00:06:02,767
You should have called me right
away to look after Jessica.

125
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:03,933
Just one case of beer,

126
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:06,967
and I'll be up all night
keeping watch.

127
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,867
You talk too much.

128
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:11,000
Just go find my husband and kid!

129
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:12,433
All right, all right.

130
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:13,600
Relax.

131
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,067
I'll find them.

132
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:19,833
Make sure of that.

133
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,567
I haven't failed yet, Hazel.

134
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,133
Yes, Sarge.

135
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:37,267
I'm going with my friend
to file a report.

136
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,233
All right, Sarge.

137
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:41,400
Thank you.

138
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:42,633
Our problem now

139
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:47,000
is how we're going to get past
Jeffrey and Andrea.

140
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,333
Jessica is calling.

141
00:06:54,467 --> 00:06:57,000
Oh, Jessica.

142
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:59,033
Yes, Dad. I'm already here.

143
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:00,300
I escaped, Mom.

144
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:01,767
<i> Thank goodness, Jessica.</i>

145
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,033
But...

146
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:06,133
Thank goodness.
How did you get in?

147
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:08,100
The gate is open.

148
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:11,133
Jessica, be careful
getting inside the house.

149
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:14,467
<i>Andrea and Jeffrey
are in the pool area.</i>

150
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:16,000
I know, Coleen.

151
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:20,133
I'm hiding right now
because Jeffrey is here.

152
00:07:20,267 --> 00:07:21,833
<i> What?</i>

153
00:07:21,967 --> 00:07:24,400
Jessica, be careful, please.

154
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:25,300
<i> Yes, Coleen.</i>

155
00:07:28,967 --> 00:07:31,233
Close your eyes.

156
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:33,433
No peeking, okay?

157
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:34,667
Okay.

158
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,867
What is it?

159
00:07:38,133 --> 00:07:39,867
Wait.

160
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,900
Here you go.

161
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,000
There.

162
00:07:50,667 --> 00:07:51,733
It's beautiful.

163
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:53,467
Perfect.

164
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,367
I thought it was something else.

165
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,733
Thank you.

166
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:57,967
But...

167
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:58,867
What's this about?

168
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,567
Why did you give me this?

169
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,300
Why carrots?

170
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:05,967
Exactly 10 years ago,
I went with Mom to the market.

171
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:09,067
And on our way home,
she told me to go back

172
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,700
because she forgot
to buy something.

173
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,233
I also remember the vendor
I bought from...

174
00:08:15,267 --> 00:08:16,567
She was so grumpy.

175
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,267
Then she yelled at me.

176
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:22,000
And you know what?
I was stunned.

177
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:24,733
Because she was incredibly
beautiful.

178
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:26,200
And then...

179
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,533
I smiled at her.

180
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:30,100
Then the thing I bought...

181
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:31,700
She threw it at me, the...

182
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:32,600
Carrots.

183
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:36,867
Do you remember?

184
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,900
Do you still remember that?

185
00:08:39,033 --> 00:08:39,667
Of course.

186
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,833
I could never forget that day.

187
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:44,133
That day...

188
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,867
That was the day I fell in love
with you.

189
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,433
Why are you crying?

190
00:08:51,567 --> 00:08:54,000
- Why are you crying?
- Because...

191
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:55,533
Let me.

192
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,367
Stop crying now.

193
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,467
You're such a crybaby.

194
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:04,033
Jeffrey, you look like Dad.

195
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:05,033
Why are you crying?

196
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,567
It's okay.

197
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,100
You're so beautiful.

198
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:10,167
Why are you making me cry?

199
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,200
Let's go.

200
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:12,333
Come on.

201
00:09:13,633 --> 00:09:14,667
You're making me cry.

202
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:30,633
Hey!

203
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,167
Who are you?

204
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,767
Sweetie, why?

205
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:57,100
Please stop fighting,
Auntie Andrea.

206
00:09:57,233 --> 00:09:59,167
It's bad.

207
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:02,400
We know that, Tetay.

208
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:05,133
But in families,

209
00:10:05,267 --> 00:10:08,433
sometimes things like this
can't be avoided.

210
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:12,333
Your Aunt Coleen
can be really stubborn.

211
00:10:12,467 --> 00:10:16,533
Because she met up
with your dad?

212
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:21,000
I heard Dad and Mom
talking about it once.

213
00:10:21,133 --> 00:10:23,867
I understand Aunt Coleen.

214
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:28,433
I was the same way
before I met Dad.

215
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:30,133
It was sad, Auntie.

216
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:37,867
That's why I hope you'll
let Aunt Coleen see him.

217
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:41,633
Whatever bad thing Grandpa
did to you,

218
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:44,233
I hope you can forgive him.

219
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:47,767
Just like how I forgave my dad.

220
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:58,000
Tetay, it's different
between you and your dad.

221
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:01,933
Your dad didn't leave you
for someone else.

222
00:11:02,067 --> 00:11:05,500
The pain we're going through...

223
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,733
It's deeper.

224
00:11:09,867 --> 00:11:13,333
When it no longer hurts,

225
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:15,967
I hope you can forgive Grandpa.

226
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,400
So that all of you
can finally make peace.

227
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,200
Didang.

228
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:29,167
- Ma'am.
- Where are they?

229
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:34,733
Andrea is changing her clothes.

230
00:11:34,867 --> 00:11:38,433
I accidentally spilled syrup
from the custard cake on her.

231
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:39,667
Wait.

232
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,200
Was there still syrup
left on the custard cake?

233
00:11:42,367 --> 00:11:43,467
There was.

234
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,033
Can you believe it?

235
00:11:45,167 --> 00:11:46,100
She would look for you!

236
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:48,233
So I distracted her.

237
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:49,633
I spilled it on her.

238
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:53,800
That's why she went upstairs
with Tetay.

239
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:55,067
Well, I guess that worked out.

240
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:55,900
Didang.

241
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:57,633
- Yes?
- Good news.

242
00:11:57,767 --> 00:11:59,967
Jessica has finally
escaped her mom.

243
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,500
Coleen!

244
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:03,300
- Who's this?
- Really?

245
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:04,067
Oh, no!

246
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:14,167
What?

247
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:22,333
What?

248
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:24,867
Have you been watching
Abel's house?

249
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,500
<i> Not just watching.</i>

250
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:28,833
I broke into the house.

251
00:12:28,967 --> 00:12:31,967
But Manuel and Jessica
aren't there.

252
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,467
Why don't you try
at Felma's house?

253
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,900
Yes, classmate.

254
00:12:36,033 --> 00:12:38,500
I'm actually here now.

255
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,867
Oh, good.

256
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,300
So now what? Then get moving!

257
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:43,700
<i> Relax.</i>

258
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,200
I've got you.

259
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,400
Hello, Bro.

260
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:51,833
Jessica escaped Hazel.

261
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:53,200
Bro, good to hear that.

262
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:54,833
But be extra careful.

263
00:12:54,967 --> 00:12:58,233
Andrea and Jeffrey
might catch you.

264
00:12:58,367 --> 00:12:59,767
Jeff, let me explain.

265
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:02,100
Explain?

266
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:04,033
Your classmate's been waiting
outside for a while now.

267
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,667
She said she's been texting you,
but you're not replying.

268
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,767
Aren't you even
a little embarrassed?

269
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:09,833
No, Jeffrey. It's okay.

270
00:13:09,967 --> 00:13:12,300
Maybe Coleen's phone
is on silent mode.

271
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:16,167
I wasn't able to tell her
that I'll come visit her.

272
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,100
Hi, Ma'am.

273
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:21,233
I'm Jane.

274
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,633
Coleen's classmate.

275
00:13:27,233 --> 00:13:28,833
By the way, Mom.

276
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:30,600
She's a transferee.

277
00:13:30,733 --> 00:13:33,500
She's a new friend
of mine and Rona.

278
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,067
What brings you here, Jane?

279
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,533
You've been waiting outside.

280
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,433
I've been absent for two days.

281
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:42,700
I just wanted to ask Coleen
for the notes.

282
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,967
- Jeff.
- Where's Tetay?

283
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,533
Is she still
in the comfort room?

284
00:13:47,667 --> 00:13:48,633
I left her in my room.

285
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:52,567
You told me you wanted
alone time with Daisy.

286
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:56,567
Who is she?

287
00:13:58,467 --> 00:13:59,700
She's my classmate, Andrea.

288
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:00,500
Her name is Jane.

289
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,333
Hi.

290
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:05,933
You must be Andrea.

291
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:07,133
Nice meeting you.

292
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:11,700
You're so beautiful.

293
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,600
English speaking?

294
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:16,900
Your voice sounds familiar
to me.

295
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,900
Why?

296
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:23,367
Can you speak?

297
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,300
In English?

298
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:27,900
What do you want me to say?

299
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,933
I've heard your voice before.

300
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:34,300
You know, Andrea, since you talk
to different people every day,

301
00:14:34,433 --> 00:14:37,133
it's possible that the voices
you hear sound similar.

302
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:39,233
No, Jeff, that's not it.

303
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:40,433
I remember before,

304
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:42,067
I had a fight
with an English-speaking girl.

305
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,633
It was the same.

306
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,867
That's why I also ended up
speaking in English.

307
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,533
I really can't forget that.

308
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:49,300
She sounded exactly like you.

309
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,500
I just can't remember.

310
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:54,400
What was that?

311
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:58,867
Jane, have we ever
argued before?

312
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:05,167
<i>We lived for a long time
without you all those years!</i>

313
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:06,933
<i>So we'll keep going without you!</i>

314
00:15:07,067 --> 00:15:08,033
<i> It's fine!</i>

315
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:09,967
<i>Stay with your worthless family!</i>

316
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,567
<i> Go rot together in hell!</i>

317
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:13,967
<i> Hello?</i>

318
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,933
I understand you.

319
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:25,833
<i>You've experienced
having a father, right?</i>

320
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,667
<i>And you got hurt
because of him.</i>

321
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,833
<i>Isn't that the feeling you
don't want Coleen to go through?</i>

322
00:15:29,967 --> 00:15:31,167
<i> Because between the two of us,</i>

323
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:34,033
<i>you were the one who was hurt
the most when Dad left us.</i>

324
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,967
Bro...

325
00:15:36,133 --> 00:15:38,967
The wound I left
on my kids is so deep.

326
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:42,900
Especially with Andeng.

327
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,933
<i> That's impossible, Andrea.</i>

328
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:55,167
<i>It's Jane's first time
coming here.</i>

329
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:05,133
Why is Jessica with them?

330
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:06,000
What? What? What? What?

331
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,033
Bro, calm down.

332
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,233
What's happening?

333
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,867
Bro, I think Jessica was caught.

334
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:17,233
Maybe I'm just imagining things.

335
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:18,833
Just let it go, okay?
Sorry about that.

336
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,700
Oh, okay.

337
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:23,567
How about this?

338
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,300
Have some dessert first.

339
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,767
Oh.

340
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:30,533
Here's Ma'am Felma's specialty,
the chocolate custard cake.

341
00:16:30,667 --> 00:16:32,133
You'll like this, Jessie.

342
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:36,500
Jessie, is that right?

343
00:16:36,633 --> 00:16:39,200
Jane, Didang.

344
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,667
She just said that.

345
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,733
Where did you get Jessie from?

346
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,467
Didang, are you deaf or what?

347
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,133
Didang, please go pick up Tetay.

348
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:49,767
She hasn't eaten yet.

349
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,500
Yes, Ma'am.

350
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,567
And clean your ears.

351
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:54,867
- I will do it right away.
- Jessie.

352
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,300
Oh, it's raining.

353
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,133
Let's have dessert inside.

354
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:01,933
Bring the food inside.

355
00:17:02,067 --> 00:17:02,833
Yes, I will.

356
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:04,500
I got it.

357
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:05,600
Let's go.

358
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:06,867
Bro, I'm about to stir up
trouble

359
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,833
with Felma's family again.

360
00:17:08,967 --> 00:17:10,767
Bro, just chill.
Bro, chill, chill.

361
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:11,600
Calm down.

362
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:15,100
Bro, they're gone.

363
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,767
Oh, no! Now it's raining!

364
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:25,700
It's so good, Mom.

365
00:18:27,267 --> 00:18:28,100
Perfect.

366
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:30,467
Tetay fell asleep.

367
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,400
It's really so good.

368
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:32,667
There you go.

369
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,800
My niece got tired

370
00:18:35,933 --> 00:18:38,633
because you and Daisy were busy
having a moment.

371
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:40,333
Daisy.

372
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:41,433
I was just joking, Daisy.

373
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:42,367
I was just joking.

374
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,033
Karma's so fast! Digital!

375
00:18:50,167 --> 00:18:51,433
- Oh, really?
- Hey, hey!

376
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:52,633
Wait, I'm still getting some.

377
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:53,367
Mom!

378
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,300
- Is that so?
- Andrea!

379
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:56,800
- Oh, really?
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

380
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:57,733
I was just joking.

381
00:18:57,867 --> 00:18:59,033
This is new!

382
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:01,467
She's going to put
cake on me, Mom.

383
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,500
Later, you two
will start fighting again.

384
00:19:03,633 --> 00:19:04,900
Who wouldn't get mad
with a face like that?

385
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:07,233
Ouch! What?

386
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:08,333
Oh, gosh.

387
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:09,267
You two are so silly.

388
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,200
So delicious!

389
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:15,567
They're really playful.

390
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:20,767
You guys must've had so much fun
growing up together, right?

391
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:21,967
I'm jealous.

392
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:25,333
You had Dad with you
while you were growing up.

393
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:27,167
That's also something
to be jealous of.

394
00:19:47,767 --> 00:19:49,400
<i> Dear, what happened?</i>

395
00:19:49,533 --> 00:19:51,200
<i> Did your siblings catch you?</i>

396
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:54,767
Stay over there!

397
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:35,700
There's a thief!

398
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,433
<i> They must know about it!</i>

399
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:42,033
Felma!

400
00:20:42,167 --> 00:20:44,000
<i>But I'll get caught
that I'm here.</i>

401
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,633
<i> How am I going to tell them?</i>

402
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:50,667
What's your problem?

403
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,533
Get away from behind me, Jeff!

404
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:53,200
I'm just eating.

405
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,133
You're getting too close.

406
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:55,300
You're going to spill
something on me.

407
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:56,167
I just went closer.

408
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:57,067
You're going to spill on me.

409
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,100
I can see you.

410
00:20:58,233 --> 00:20:59,600
She's overreacting, Mom.

411
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:00,133
Look at her.

412
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:01,633
You, two.

413
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:02,333
That's enough.

414
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:03,733
It's his fault, Mom.

415
00:21:03,867 --> 00:21:06,000
You're no match with Andrea,
Jeff.

416
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:09,800
That's true, so if he ever
hurts you, tell me because...

417
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:10,833
Ouch, ouch, ouch, that hurts!

418
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:12,067
Dear, dear, that's enough.

419
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,267
She's hurting me! That hurts!

420
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,533
Mom, he really
gets on my nerves.

421
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:17,167
- Stop it already.
- You're annoying me!

422
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:19,200
Hey, the rain has stopped now!

423
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:21,367
So, Daisy,
should I drive you home?

424
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:22,900
But Tetay's sleeping.

425
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:26,233
You know, you should
stay the night.

426
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:27,967
Yes, Daisy, you can sleep here.

427
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:31,100
Poor Tetay if we end up
waking her.

428
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:32,333
Right?

429
00:21:32,467 --> 00:21:34,567
Didang, get the guest room
ready, okay?

430
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,400
Yes, Ma'am.

431
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:36,467
- Okay.
- I'll take care of that.

432
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,300
Oh, I'll go with you, Didang.

433
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:40,600
Because...

434
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:45,200
I still need to look for
the FMP sales report.

435
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:47,000
Good night, Mom.

436
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,367
Good night.

437
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:52,067
Oh, don't keep your friend
up all night, okay?

438
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,100
Her dad will pick her up
before midnight.

439
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:57,567
All right. Good night.

440
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:58,733
Good night, Andrea.

441
00:22:03,433 --> 00:22:06,333
You know, your voice really
sounds familiar to me.

442
00:22:09,167 --> 00:22:10,100
Just kidding!

443
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:10,933
- I was just joking.
- Andrea!

444
00:22:11,067 --> 00:22:11,967
Mom, don't get mad.

445
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,033
- I was just kidding.
- Let's go!

446
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:16,200
Did you get nervous, Mom?

447
00:22:16,367 --> 00:22:17,433
Andeng, would you
still eat this?

448
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:18,167
No, right?

449
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,300
Hey!

450
00:22:41,433 --> 00:22:42,533
What's that? Is someone there?

451
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:43,233
Hey!

452
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:43,967
Son, wait!

453
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:45,067
- Who are you?
- Wait!

454
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:45,900
Don't!

455
00:22:46,033 --> 00:22:47,167
Is someone there? Son, wait!

456
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:48,400
- Who are you?
- Wait!

457
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:51,067
Don't! Don't!

458
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,067
Wait!

459
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,733
Son!

460
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:55,567
- Who is he?
- Are you a thief?

461
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,367
Wait!

462
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,967
- Hold on!
- You're a thief, right?

463
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,733
- Who are you?
- Jeffrey!

464
00:23:01,867 --> 00:23:02,900
Who are you?

465
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:05,433
What are you doing
in my girlfriend's house?

466
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:08,400
You idiot! Don't try to fool us!
You're a thief!

467
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:09,533
Jeff, my son! Oh, no!

468
00:23:09,667 --> 00:23:11,700
Son, I think he's drunk.
Don't engage.

469
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:14,200
Mister, this is our house!

470
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:16,567
Wait, isn't this Amelia's house?

471
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:18,767
You're a liar!
You're stealing from us!

472
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:20,967
- Mom, call the police!
- Call the police?

473
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,800
- Call the police!
- Call the police?

474
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:25,733
Jeff! Son, son, son!

475
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:27,300
Get out of here!

476
00:23:27,433 --> 00:23:28,700
- What!
- Enough! Get out now!

477
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:31,300
Get out now!
That's enough, Jeff! Stop!

478
00:23:31,433 --> 00:23:34,300
He might have a gun.
You could get hurt.

479
00:23:34,433 --> 00:23:36,067
We should report this
to the guard!

480
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,967
Mom, all the guards here
are useless!

481
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:40,533
People have been robbed
here so many times already!

482
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:42,500
Report it to the homeowners
so they can replace them!

483
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:45,100
Yes! I will report it!

484
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,600
Yes, Alice?

485
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:55,967
So, the Airbnb owner moved
me to a bigger building of hers.

486
00:23:56,133 --> 00:23:57,167
Nice, right?

487
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:58,733
Ma'am, where should I put this?

488
00:23:58,867 --> 00:24:00,367
Just there.

489
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:03,600
But I still haven't found
Manuel and Jessica.

490
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:06,767
Oh, that Maximo guy
is really slow.

491
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,467
Not just slow.

492
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:09,700
He's useless!

493
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:11,667
He's so dumb!

494
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,367
I just really wish
you were here,

495
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:16,500
so I would have someone
to share my frustrations with.

496
00:24:16,633 --> 00:24:18,367
Of course,
a call is different from...

497
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,233
You know,
it's not the same as in person.

498
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:23,833
Well, you're so lucky,
my friend.

499
00:24:23,967 --> 00:24:27,133
Because I'm flying home
anytime now.

500
00:24:27,267 --> 00:24:28,167
What?

501
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:29,133
Seriously?

502
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:30,233
Yes.

503
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:32,900
I was thinking of starting
a business there,

504
00:24:33,033 --> 00:24:35,267
so I took
an indefinite leave here.

505
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,800
What about Charles?

506
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:37,767
Come on.

507
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:41,200
He no longer has a say
in my decisions.

508
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:43,133
That's why I divorced him,
right?

509
00:24:43,267 --> 00:24:46,267
So I can freely do
whatever I want.

510
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,133
That's great.

511
00:24:48,267 --> 00:24:49,867
Wait. Looks like the food
I ordered has arrived.

512
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,367
I'll call you back, okay?

513
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,733
Bye!

514
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:03,033
Classmate!

515
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,200
Hey! Wow, this place looks nice.

516
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:05,867
What are you doing here?

517
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:08,567
Classmate, you're upgraded.
Your new place is nice...

518
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:09,700
What are you doing here?

519
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:12,433
You've got some nerve showing up
after you messed up!

520
00:25:12,567 --> 00:25:14,033
Relax, chill!

521
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:16,067
I got away with it anyway.

522
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,100
You really don't think
things through, do you?

523
00:25:19,233 --> 00:25:19,733
Here's what you'll do.

524
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:20,967
Go back there later,

525
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:23,467
and make sure that Felma
doesn't catch you this time.

526
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,767
Classmate, your husband
and daughter aren't there.

527
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:28,933
Before I went inside,
I scoped the place out.

528
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:30,567
It's just them,
having a barbecue party.

529
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,100
Look. See?

530
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,300
There's no one
in a wheelchair with them.

531
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:44,333
Oh, no!

532
00:25:44,467 --> 00:25:45,933
I'm back to square one.

533
00:25:50,267 --> 00:25:52,133
I've hurt you so much already.

534
00:25:52,267 --> 00:25:54,967
I might even break
you and Noah apart.

535
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,700
Didn't Coleen tell you?

536
00:25:56,833 --> 00:25:59,500
Noah and I split up
before you came.

537
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:00,867
I thought you two
were going to get married.

538
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:04,733
There's only one man I see
walking me down the aisle.

539
00:26:04,867 --> 00:26:06,033
And that's you.

540
00:26:06,167 --> 00:26:09,600
I hope you all learn
to get along, Coleen.

541
00:26:09,767 --> 00:26:12,567
So you can finally experience
what it's like to have a dad.

542
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:16,067
I need someone to infiltrate
Felma's Meat Products.

543
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:19,167
We need someone who
actually knows how to scheme.

544
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,567
You have me.

545
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:23,767
Alice!

546
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:24,567
Hey!

547
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:25,400
What?

548
00:26:25,533 --> 00:26:26,333
Noah is here?

549
00:26:26,467 --> 00:26:28,067
Yes, Ma'am.

550
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,067
He wants to talk to you.

551
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:32,733
Why didn't he call or text?

552
00:26:32,867 --> 00:26:34,500
Is anyone there?

553
00:26:34,633 --> 00:26:35,667
Coleen?

554
00:26:39,267 --> 00:26:40,133
Manuel?

555
00:26:40,267 --> 00:26:41,633
Noah?
